{
  "stem": "24231.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But my father seen him in the-- in the light of the starlight outside.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he fell down on the steps.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So-- and as he was falling, his arm was in the air.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And-- and-- and he got hit through the-- through his arm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And as soon as the SS men thought they killed him, they just walked away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Well, my father got back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And at night, he called his friend who was a doctor and asked him that he was shot and if he could come over there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And so he-- he went over.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the friend bandaged him up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he came home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "In the morning, all the sudden an SS man comes in a-- with a truck for the body.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And then when-- when they saw that he was alive, they started to laugh and just walked away.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Now, coming back to-- after that, not-- not long after that, we-- we went into-- into the transport.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And that's how he wind up in Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "When we came to Theresienstadt, my father became a blacksmith.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "He got the job, and because he was pretty skill how to hoof.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "The-- the man who was running the-- the blacksmith said, yeah, you-- you-- you-- you are a good man, so I'll keep you here.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And he was hoofing all the horses, which-- which were in this so-called [NON-ENGLISH], which is the agriculture section, and-- and also horses, riding horses which the SS men were riding.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "One of the horse, I still remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was a black horse, was belong to an SS man, Rahm, who was in charge of the-- of the camp later on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I guess he was the last one.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
